The paper proposes a novel approach for local overlapping community detection using spectral methods. This falls under the broad category of network analysis and graph algorithms, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with network analysis and community detection. cs.SD (Sound) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories as they cover graph algorithms and data structures. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are less likely categories, but they may still be relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques and control theory concepts to develop the proposed approach.
